*:'''Homophones''': [[bud]] (''in some North American accents''), [[butt]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ʌt|Rhymes: -ʌt]]

===Conjunction===
'''but'''

#Introducing a clause that contrasts with or contradicts the preceding clause or sentence.
#: You told me I could do that but she said that I could not.
#: But that is not what you told me.
# Except
#: I like everything but that.

====Usage note====
*Beginning a sentence with '''but''' or any other conjunction is considered incorrect by classical grammarians, but use of the word in this way is very common.  It is however best to avoid beginning a sentence with '''but''' in formal writing.

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[however]]
*(2): [[bar]], [[except]], [[excepting]], [[excluding]], [[with the exception of]]

